    chineseText: `我的哥哥今年大学毕业了，开始找工作。他学的是计算机，所以他想找一份和计算机有关的工作。

哥哥每天在网上看招聘信息，发现了很多工作机会。有的公司要求工作经验，有的公司不要求，只要有相关专业的学历就可以。哥哥选了几家公司，发送了自己的简历。

过了几天，有两家公司给哥哥发来了面试通知。哥哥很高兴，认真准备了面试。他查了很多关于这两家公司的信息，还练习了一些常见的面试问题。

第一家公司的面试在周三上午。哥哥穿上了正式的衣服，提前半小时到了公司。面试官问了他很多问题，关于他的学习经历、项目经验和对工作的看法。哥哥回答得很认真，感觉还不错。

第二家公司的面试在周五下午。这次面试有一个技术测试，需要写一段程序。哥哥说这部分比较难，他有几道题没有做完。

等了一个星期，第一家公司通知哥哥，他通过了面试，可以去上班了。哥哥非常开心，我们全家都为他高兴。

哥哥说："找工作真的不容易，但是只要努力准备，就一定能成功。"

哥哥上班后，每天都很认真。他说，找到一份合适的工作不容易，所以更要珍惜这个机会，努力做好每一件事。`,
    englishTranslation: `My older brother graduated from university this year and started looking for a job. He studied computer science, so he wanted to find a job related to computers.

Every day, my brother looked at job listings online and found many opportunities. Some companies required work experience, while others didn't — just a relevant degree was enough. He selected a few companies and sent out his resume.

A few days later, two companies sent him interview invitations. My brother was very happy and prepared carefully for the interviews. He researched both companies thoroughly and practiced common interview questions.

The first company's interview was on Wednesday morning. My brother dressed formally and arrived at the company half an hour early. The interviewer asked him many questions about his academic background, project experience, and views on work. My brother answered seriously and felt it went well.

The second company's interview was on Friday afternoon. This interview included a technical test that required writing a program. My brother said this part was quite difficult and he didn't finish a few of the questions.

After waiting a week, the first company notified my brother that he had passed the interview and could start work. My brother was overjoyed, and our whole family was happy for him.

My brother said, "Job hunting is really not easy, but as long as you prepare hard, you will definitely succeed."

In the afternoon, Teacher Liu handed back the composition books. Many students had received high marks, but a few had not written very well. Teacher Liu said that the most important thing in writing a composition was to have your own ideas — you couldn't just write things everyone already knew.`,
    recommendedVocabulary: ["\u6bd5\u4e1a", "\u62db\u8058", "\u7b80\u5386", "\u9762\u8bd5", "\u9762\u8bd5\u5b98", "\u7ecf\u5386", "\u6280\u672f", "\u7a0b\u5e8f", "\u901a\u8fc7", "\u6210\u529f"],
